The paper discusses the development of a system that leverages knowledge graphs to semantically process scholarly knowledge. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), semantic web (cs.SI), and databases (cs.DB). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DL, followed by cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI, and cs.DB.
